==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monotony
<hw>Mo*not"o*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>monotonie</ets>. See <er>Monotonius</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
frequent recurrence of the same tone or sound, producing a dull
uniformity; absence of variety, as in speaking or singing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any irksome sameness, or want of variety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At sea, everything that breaks the <qex>monotony</qex> of the
surrounding expanse attracts attention.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monotremata</ent>⟦br⟧
